https://userinterfaces.aalto.fi/mobile-saliency/resources/mobile-saliency.pdf
Summary (what you need to pay attention to when creating an application):
1) Color. As noted in this article, in the age of visualists, it is very important that the colors of the application are harmoniously combined.
2) Text. The text in the application should be understandable to everyone, without exception, it should be short and laconic.
3) Sound. pay attention to this too. (pressing buttons)
4) Graphic visualization
5) Do not experiment with the location of the buttons. (Exit - Top Right, Search - Center)
6) Support chat
7) Ability to leave a review
/
